==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dissert
<hw>Dis*sert"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dissertus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>disserere</ets>; <ets>dis-</ets> +
<ets>serere</ets> to join, connect: cf. F. <ets>disserter</ets>. See
<er>Series</er>.]</ety> <def>To discourse or dispute; to discuss.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We have <qex>disserted</qex> upon it a little longer than was
necessary.</q> <rj><qau>Jeffrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dissertate</ent>⟦br⟧
